snippet.title: Java Queue Tutorial - Learn how to use Queues in Java
snippet.description:
New course coming soon! Learn Java Fast launches on July 1st, 2020. Stay informed and join the waitlist: https://course.alexlorenlee.com/courses/learn-java-fast

- A queue is an object that lets you store data like a line for a restaurant. First in line gets first dibs.

A queue is just a line. People stand in line and get fed in order. Queues in java take the next value in the queue. To take the next value in a java queue, do:

q.poll();

Or look at the next value in the queue by:

q.peek();

This queue java code can be tricky at first... But SURELY you'll get it :) If you followed along, congrats! You learned-by-doing!

I hope you enjoyed this java queue tutorial! I like to have a nice mix of tutorials and actual projects for you all :)

Do you want to learn how to write java code from scratch, in Java? Check out my Java Tutorial For Beginners: https://youtu.be/woJb2hAfkO0

Was this able to help you learn about the queue data structure in java? -
